{"title": "Bloomberg-backed group plans pro-immigration campaign", "url": "http://nypost.com/2017/02/21/bloomberg-backed-group-plans-pro-immigration-campaign/", "text": "A Michael Bloomberg-backed group is organizing a massive pro-immigration campaign this week, a direct challenge to President Trump\u2019s hardline stance on the controversial issue.\n\n\u201cImmigration is top of the agenda politically, but the national discussion often bears little resemblance to the facts on the ground,\u201d said the Partnership for a New American Economy\u2019s executive director, Jeremy Robbins, according to Politico.\n\n\u201cIn community after community and industry after industry, immigration is helping America and American workers,\u201d he added.\n\nThe effort is one of the first well-funded, well-organized nationwide efforts aimed squarely at stopping Trump from carrying out a temporary travel ban and building a border wall between the US and Mexico.\n\nThe campaign features 100 nationwide events, beginning this week, along with an ad campaign with spots airing in Houston, Dallas, Las Vegas and Miami.\n\nIt also features the coming together of Republicans and Trump supporters to help push for immigration reform, rather than the deportation of illegal immigrants.\n\nIt is unknown how much the billionaire ex-Big Apple mayor has donated to the group \u2014 or how much he\u2019s willing to spend to stop Trump\u2019s immigration efforts.", "source": "New York Post", "publish_date": "2017-02-21", "type": "article"}